<br>
Mages are some of the best PLers for chars in their 30's to upper 40's. What you do is this:<br>
<br>
1) Go to some place where your pet can handle the mob on its own and is still blue+ to the cleric. DL is a good place. NOTE: Bring lots of Malachite.<br>
2) Let your pet beat on the mob until its almost dead and starts to flee. Cleric watches this happens and meds.<br>
3) Reclaim your pet at this point.<br>
4) Cleric nukes the mob dead while mage is getting a new pet for the next mob.<br>
5) Rinse and Repeat.<br>
<br>
Nandail<br>
Retired Mage from Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kalamos>Kalamos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 456<br> <font color=#333333>(1/8/03 9:47:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8388.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Can mages powerlevel clerics?</span><hr size=1> Absolutely.<br>
<br>
Pull a MOB with yer Mage using a debuff.  Have an Earth pet beat said MOB down to a sliver of health.  Click an instant reclaim item.  Nuke MOB dead with the Cleric.  Summon another pet, rinse and repeat.<br>
<br>
I made my girlfriend start her Cleric over on a new account before they allowed toon transfers.  So I PLed her to 50 in no time using this method.<br>
<br>
OR ... you could just group and kill stuff green or blue to the Mage but red to the Cleric.  Lvl 40s will get exp with a lvl 54 grouped.<br>
